node.text: from @viaerocenter: ATTN: The Cody Johnson show scheduled for tonight at the Viaero Center in Kearney, Nebraska has unfortunately been cancelled due to a mechanical failure at the Viaero Center, which caused high standing water. The result of which has created a severe safety issue because of the amount of voltage used in order to put on the show. The venue has decided that the safety concerns for patrons, as well as all bands, crews, and employees, are too great to proceed with the show. All ticket buyers will be refunded at the point of purchase.

node.text:
Attention #COJONation! Tickets are now on sale for Dear Rodeo: The Cody Johnson Story, coming to theaters nationwide, with limited screenings from August 10!

The film captures every emotion I've felt over the past 20 years – whether standing in the back of the chute at the rodeo or singing about it in front of 75,000 fans. It shows you all the highs and the lows that come from following the dreams you cling to and the dreams you let go of. 

Book now at codyjohnsonfilm.com #DEARRODEO

@wrangler @resistol1927

node.text: Team Roping was Cody‘s heart and his passion. One of his final wishes was to have this event and raise money to help others going through cancer treatment. Please join us May 29-31 at the Leon County Expo Center in Buffalo, Texas. Help us share Cody’s story. #nessmithstrong #cowboy #teamroping

node.text: Back in 2019, I had the honor and privilege to play the @theryman and make my mark on country music. I'm pleased to announce that we'll be returning to Nashville on June 19th to play for y'all once again. Tickets go on sale this Friday. Link in story.

node.text: All the things that hurt were starting to pay off. Records started being broken, and I was having the time of my life. I couldn't have done it without #COJONation. Watch this exclusive clip from the #DearRodeo documentary to hear more.

node.text: I was broke, but I didn't care because I was chasing a dream. I turned to music not only to spread the message of rodeo, but also to make a little money. Listen to more of my story in this exclusive clip from the #DearRodeo documentary.

#COJONation, tonight is the night! See Dear Rodeo: The Cody Johnson Story in theaters nationwide!

Get tickets at codyjohnsonfilm.com
